-## 8. Output Artifact
+## 8. Complexity Review
+
+> **When**: After decomposition (Step 6) and Priority Stack gate (Step 7) pass — before presenting the artifact to the user for final approval.
+
+Run a focused simplicity pass on the draft artifact. The goal is to **remove unnecessary complexity before `/develop` commits to it**.
+
+### Checks
+
+| Check | Question |
+|---|---|
+| **Scope pruning** | Can any PBI be cut or deferred without reducing core value? Apply MoSCoW — drop or defer all "Could" items that lack a stated business case. |
+| **PBI merging** | Are any PBIs so small or tightly coupled that separating them adds overhead with no independence benefit? Merge them. |
+| **Requirement redundancy** | Do any requirements overlap or restate the same constraint? Consolidate. |
+| **Over-engineering** | Does any PBI imply a pattern (e.g., plugin system, event bus) whose complexity isn't yet justified by scale? Flag and simplify. |
+| **Assumption debt** | Are `[ASSUMPTION - unverified]` items blocking more than one PBI? Resolve or escalate before proceeding. |
+
+### Output
+
+- Update the artifact in-place and append a brief `## Complexity Review` section listing what was removed/merged and why.
+- If changes are significant, re-run the Priority Stack gate (Step 7) on the revised artifact.
+- **Self-review**: Apply the review criteria from `/review` (Priority Stack Gate + Pre-Mortem) to the final draft. Document any findings in a `## Self-Review` section in the artifact.
+- Set `status: draft` in the frontmatter when the self-review passes with no 🔴 Critical findings. This signals the artifact is ready to present to the user for final review.
+- **Do not set `status: reviewed` yet** — that is set only after the user explicitly approves the artifact in Step 9.
+
+---
